args: At a point in which my brother's promise\nwas the only thing that kept me going...
My father paid me a visit.
Our father is still alive in your world?!
Yes. In our world, my brother never\nwent to the Binding Ruins.
Therefore, my father never lost his life.
Having been banished from the kingdom,\nhe set out to find a way to save it.

Specifically, he sought a way to stop the
Other's resurrection. To this end, he
planned to use the Dawnshard to open
channels to alternate worlds.
When my father approached me,\nhe already possessed the Dawnshard.
But using it would require\nvast amounts of mana.
That is why he had been searching for me:\nBecause of the mana I possess in my\nrole as the Auspex.

The Auspex is a person of pure heart who
possesses divine mana. Perhaps only one
blessed by mana itself can hope to wield
the Dawnshard.
So where is this Dawnshard, anyway?
I mean, you got the one from your world,\nbut where's the one from OURS?
A wise question, Luca; it would indeed be\ndangerous to let so powerful an artifact\nfall into enemy hands.
Plus if WE have it, we can totally use\nthe sucker to win the day!
Alas, my father chose not to share the\nknowledge of where it could be found.
He seemed to believe it better to keep\nit secret. And while I wondered at his\nreluctance, I did not press the issue.
Then let's put aside the question of the\nDawnshard's whereabouts for now.
So if I'm understanding this correctly,\nyou used the Dawnshard he gave you\nto create a bridge between our worlds.
Yes—but there is more to it than that.
I have visited numerous worlds\nbesides this one.
The journey was indeed brutal.\nSo much so, I nearly lost myself.
Once again I failed to save them.\nOnce again, I watched them die.
(Sometimes they passed before my eyes.\nSometimes...while in my arms.)
(No matter where I went,\nit always ended in death.)
I can't save anyone or anything.\nYet somehow I continue to live.
Dear brother, I don't understand!\nWhat meaning can there be in the\nsurvival of one so useless as I?
How much better would things be\nif only I could die in their place!
...A dragon?!\nIt's come all the way here?!
(If this dragon is here, it means the others\nwho were fighting to buy me time...)
(If I sustain enough damage here that\nI am unable to project my consciousness\nback to my home world...)
(My empty body will perish soon after.)
(That would be the end result of all that\nI have fought for. If I think of it in such\nterms, it doesn't seem so bad.)
*pant* *pant* Let's hide here for now.\nWe just have to hope it moves on.
Why did you save me?\nDo you know who I am?
You fight against fate, do you not?
It is not so hard to figure. After all,\nI am here, yet you are also me.
You certainly pieced that together quickly.
I have been making a study of all the\npossible ways I could save this world.
Alas, I failed to locate ＂the Sacred Shard\nwith the power to change causality.＂
I do not know from whence you hail,\nbut I am glad to have met a version of me\nwho managed to cross between worlds.
Your mission is a crucial one;\nI cannot permit it to falter here!
What is the difference between us?\nWhy don't YOU travel between worlds?!
I have been doing this for so long,\nand yet have accomplished nothing.\nI am weak. Useless. ...Pathetic.
My brother protected me, and everyone\nsung my praises as the Auspex—but no\none knew how truly powerless I am!
No matter how many worlds I visit,\nnothing changes—I lose everyone\nI care about and end up alone!
It's naught but pain and misery.\nI have lost myself, and no longer\neven know why I walk this path.
Why is this MY burden to bear?!\nYou are Zethia as much as I,\nso why can YOU not take it up?!
...Even I do not truly know you.
We may both be ＂Zethia,＂ but that does not\nmean I know you. You have seen things—\ndone things—that I can only imagine.
Is that not proof we are in fact different?
Even when you are at the very end of\nyour own self, you still cling to a hope\nthat you would see realized.
Don't worry, I got this! Go and keep\nyour promise to {player_name}!
I'm puttin' all of my chips on ya,\nso go save the future from the Other!
No one ought to be alone, so go\nfind the people you care about!
Protecting the Auspex is a Paladyn's\nsworn duty. So in death—as in life—\nI shall ever be your shield. Haaaah!
Hey, you KNOW I'm always with you!\nAlive, dead, whatever—ol' Notte's gotcha.
So don't cry, okay? All that does\nis fog up your eyes.
W-we'll meet again, Zethia... I swear...
At first, this was a hope all my own.\nBut I suppose things are different now.
And though I am weak and alone,\nI am not TRULY alone.
For those I've lost—in all the worlds—\nhave entrusted their hopes in me.
Only the weak can wish to be strong.
So grow strong—strong enough that\nyou will never lose anything again!
That is a different dragon than before.\nIf it gets inside, the castle will be lost.
Yes—but you need not be the one\nto shoulder that duty.
It is time for you to quit this world.
And leave you to fight alone?\nNo! That is madness!
It may be madness, at that.\nAnd yet, it will be done!
We may both be Zethia, but you are YOU,\nand I have my own duties to bear.
Your wish is the same one we all share.\nThat's why we entrust our hopes to you.
Heavy lies that burden on your brow.\nAt times you may resent it, or wish\nto abandon it.
But do not let despair win the day.\nFor this burden is what proves that\nyou are not alone in this fight.
It is proof that among all Zethias,\nyou are truly special.
Now begone, I beg of you!
Go, Zethia. Save my brother...\nand the future!
